title: Director and Project Manager; ManeFrame; Operating Systems for Military Vehicles
description: Date: October 2000-July 2007 Role: .Net Developer Project: SharePoint/Span Top of the System, Report Management Zone Early 2004 Recruiting Command and the Army began to migrate from the old systems known as Army Recruiting Information Support System. I was tasked by the Chief of Staff to create a newer, more user friendly system that would immediately populate the servers and allow for instantaneous data to migrate as it happens, or as the keys were stroked. We also wanted to stop having the entire Department of Defense Clogging up Outlook on a regular basis but also have a system where we can login and see what is going on just about everywhere so long as those individuals either held the clearance or were given the rights to access. That’s where SharePoint came into play. I and my team from ground zero built the Army’s SharePoint, Top of the System and Report Management Zone. These were 3rd party builds however they all were synched together and it allowed for any person to go in at anytime and pull any data on anything anywhere at any time. Though at first there were some growing pains mainly with users but in the end we worked through all the trouble tickets and the Command and DoD operates 100% with these systems now and the others have been done away with.
